    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.13"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 8-45.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have no early prospect of going to <unclear>Chicago</unclear> Am half-or 3/4- vacationing, now, as Laura is, during July; we stay in the country here with Beastie + Foxy, we swim in the river, + we see noone<sic>no one</sic> but our Negro-Indian neighbors. I am deep in Indian reading now &#8212; Iraquois<sic>Iroquois</sic>, Cherokee, Shawnee etc. &#8212; also (less) deep in Colonial (dependency) reading.</p>
                
                <p>Often comes the desire to have time with you &#8212; oftener than you suspect, I imagine.&#8212;And I never did have that evening with your wife + you! and never met your daughter.&#8212; Both of us wish you could visit us here &#8212; This, meaning you or all of you.</p>
                
                <p>I heard of the blotting-out of <unclear/> at work. Senseless, so governmental!</p>
                
                <p>You seem (in my awareness or imagination) to be always a flowing spring, + nearer to the profounds which the <unclear>lutians</unclear> knew than anyone else.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>All my wishes &#8212;</salute>
                HM Collier
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Box 312 Route 1</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><unclear>Vilma</unclear> Va</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
            </div1>
